    "top_event": "Personnel pulled overboard during blind crane lift",
    "incident_type": "LTA (>3 days)",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Crane operator responded immediately to all stop command",
      "Injured person grabbed tagline and became untangled",
      "Injured person swam to ladder and climbed to platform",
      "Rope rescue performed by rescue team",
      "Injured person transported to medic's office",
      "Injured person transported by SAR helicopter to UTMB in Galveston, Texas"
    ],
    "summary": "On May 5, 2016, at 1339 hours, an injured person's right leg became entangled in a 24-foot tagline during a blind crane lift of a cargo box from the Safe Welding Area to the pipe rack on the Perdido platform. The momentum of the cargo box pulled the injured person over the water despite the crane operator's immediate response to the all stop command. The injured person fell 106 feet into the Gulf of Mexico but was rescued and transported for medical evaluation.",
